article.headline: Tennessee Tech 82, Tenn.-Martin 74
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Amadi McKenzie led a balanced scoring attack with 19 points and Tennessee Tech beat Tennessee-Martin 82-74 Thursday night. Tech (14-9, 10-4 Ohio Valley Conference) built a 19-point lead in the second half in winning its eighth straight. McKenzie hit 7-of-9 floor shots and chipped in with seven rebounds. Belton Rivers, the league's scoring leader at 18.2, had 16 points. Anthony Fisher scored 14 and had seven rebounds and Antjuan Koger added 10. Tennessee-Martin (6-19, 4-11) was led by Cleve Woodfork with 20 points and a team-high seven rebounds. Zerek Knight scored 14 and reserves Will Lewis and Joseph Bailey had 10 each. The Golden Eagles shot 52.1 percent to 43.9 percent for Tennessee-Martin. Tech hit 27-of-42 free throws to 18-of-26 for the Skyhawks.
